history.content: I get imposter syndrome all the time, and I guess I'm relatively "successful"; everyone here is so amazing that it can be easy to feel like you're not. But you did get in here! You're amazing too! You are intelligent and capable, and Berkeley would not have accepted you if you weren't.

children.subject:
You are an A+ person. You're a Cal Bear, no one can take that from you :)

You're part of my family, as we're all one big family. You WERE accepted, so welcome to the family, and get that degree, keep grinding, improving, and enjoying this experience, and you'll get your goals one day fam

history.content:
I was reading College Confidential and I saw something interested from CalTech, they were asking whether they would be able to manage being at CalTech and people said those who are accepted are already incredibly vetted and the school knows they can succeed.

Does this feeling happen at Berkeley?

Sometimes I get impostor syndrome as I see people do really well on tests and classes, get really good internships like Big 4 or Jane Street, others get into really cool research, while others start their own companies. It's kind of easy to feel inadequate at Berkeley.
history.subject: Does Anybody Feel Like They Shouldn't Have Been Accepted to UC Berkeley or CS/EECS?
